The commissioner shall require the following of a self-insured employer-organized association group:
An actuarial certification by a member of the American Academy of Actuaries of the adequacy of the proposed rates funding arrangements of the group;
Specific reinsurance ensuring the solvency of the funding arrangement;
A demonstration of capital and surplus as follows:
Initial financial requirements. Every self-insured employer-organized association shall demonstrate initial capital and surplus equal to the greater of:
Five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000);
Two percent (2%) of projected annual contribution revenues on the first one hundred fifty million dollars ($150,000,000) of contributions and one percent (1%) of projected annual contributions on the contributions in excess of one hundred fifty million dollars ($150,000,000); or
An amount equal to the sum of eight percent (8%) of projected annual health care expenditures except those paid on a capitated basis or managed hospital payment basis and four percent (4%) of projected annual hospital expenditures paid on a managed hospital payment basis.
Continuing financial requirements. Every self-insured employer-organized association shall demonstrate ongoing capital and surplus equal to the greater of:
Five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000);
Two percent (2%) of annual contribution revenues, as reported on the most recent annual financial statement filed with the commissioner, on the first one hundred fifty million dollars ($150,000,000) of contributions and one percent (1%) of annual premiums on the contributions in excess of one hundred fifty million dollars ($150,000,000); or
An amount equal to the sum of eight percent (8%) of projected annual health care expenditures except those paid on a capitated basis or managed hospital payment basis and four percent (4%) of annual hospital expenditures paid on a managed hospital payment basis, as reported on the most recent financial statement filed with the commissioner; and
A fidelity bond for the administrator and a fidelity bond for the service company in forms and amounts prescribed by the commissioner.
